<subSubSection id="47DE21C8A8EECB42B61D4F26F92A9107" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C3B23EA2A922C2D71438E76783E8C53E" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
In the original diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="ABB6439645B9EE2AA2615940B409D452" class="Arachnida" family="Sphaerochthoniidae" genus="Sphaerochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphaerochthonius</taxonomicName>
(as well as in the accompanying key to the genera of 
<taxonomicName id="185A0547D3264BC2F07133BEED9D911D" class="Arachnida" family="Hypochthoniidae" genus="Hypochthoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hypochthoniidae</taxonomicName>
), Berlese (1910) mentions monodactyly of the legs as one of the main characters. An examination of the type species (
<taxonomicName id="A6FC38D916E460F7A8E203BE660CCE13" class="Arachnida" family="Sphaerochthoniidae" genus="Sphaerochthonius" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidus">S. splendidus</taxonomicName>
) demonstrates, however, that his Observation is incorrect. 
<taxonomicName id="E70581260EFDB134C23CB3120BC8A66E" class="Arachnida" family="Sphaerochthoniidae" genus="Sphaerochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sphaerochthonius</taxonomicName>
is tridactylous, although the lateral claws appear to be very thin and are easily overlooked. The claw segment has a characteristic shape that reminds of 
<taxonomicName id="7FDBF6015D57306E50B6B1D9008D1025" class="Arachnida" family="Protoplophoridae" genus="Cryptoplophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cryptoplophora</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="563165F486303039A7063CD2903DFF4C" class="Arachnida" family="Protoplophoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Protoplophoridae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
